---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "How to Actually Get 2026 Global Football Tournament Tickets",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "hammaadworks"
  },
  "datePublished": "2026-06-10",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "cupcal"
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Buy 2026 Global Tournament Tickets" description="A no-nonsense guide to the official ticket rollout, pricing tiers, and avoiding secondary market traps.">
  <main class="cyber-grid min-h-screen py-20 px-4">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl relative z-20">
      <a href="/blog" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 mb-8 inline-block font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm border border-indigo-500/30 px-4 py-2 rounded-full backdrop-blur-sm">← All Guides</a>
      
      <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg lg:prose-xl max-w-none prose-headings:font-black prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-indigo-400">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6 leading-tight drop-shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(255,255,255,0.2)]" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">
          How to Actually Get 2026 Global Tournament Tickets (Without Getting Scammed)
        </h1>
        
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-slate-400 mb-12 font-medium border-b border-white/10 pb-6">
          <span>By hammaadworks</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>June 10, 2026</span>
        </div>

        <p class="lead text-2xl text-slate-300 font-medium">
          You've seen the schedule. You know where your team is playing. Now comes the hard part: getting inside the stadium.
        </p>

        <p class="text-slate-300">
          The 2026 Global Tournament is the biggest sporting event in history. With 104 matches spread across three massive countries, the logistics are a nightmare—and scalpers know it. This guide is built to help you navigate the official portal and secure your seat safely.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">1. Do Not Buy From Resellers (Yet)</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          If you see tickets on third-party sites or random social media accounts right now, <strong>they are speculative</strong>. The organizers have a strict policy: tickets are tied to the purchaser's ID via the official mobile app. Buying third-party tickets this early is a massive financial risk. 
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">2. The Official Ticketing Portal</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          There is only one place to buy official tickets. You need to create an account on the global governing body's website and register your interest immediately. 
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          Tickets are typically sold in three phases:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 marker:text-indigo-500">
          <li><strong>Phase 1 (Random Selection Draw):</strong> You apply for matches. If demand exceeds supply (it will), a lottery decides who gets to buy them.</li>
          <li><strong>Phase 2 (First Come, First Served):</strong> The leftovers from Phase 1 go on sale. You will sit in a digital waiting room for hours. Have multiple devices ready.</li>
          <li><strong>Phase 3 (Last Minute):</strong> Released weeks before the tournament as federations return unsold allocations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">3. Know Your Pricing Tiers</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          Stadium seats are generally categorized into three tiers:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 marker:text-indigo-500">
          <li><strong>Category 1:</strong> The best seats in the house (along the touchlines). Expect to pay premium prices.</li>
          <li><strong>Category 2:</strong> Corners and lower sections behind the goals. A solid middle ground.</li>
          <li><strong>Category 3:</strong> High up behind the goals. These are the most affordable and hardest to get in the lottery.</li>
          <li><em class="text-slate-400">Note: Category 4 exists, but it is strictly reserved for residents of the host countries (USA, Canada, Mexico).</em></li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-16 p-8 bg-indigo-900/30 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-3xl backdrop-blur-md">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">💡</span> Pro Tip: The Team-Specific Series (TST)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-indigo-200 mb-0">
            If you only care about one country (e.g., Mexico or England), apply for a TST ticket in Phase 1. It guarantees you a ticket to every match your team plays, regardless of where they travel.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          Patience is your best weapon. Register your email on the official site, put money aside now, and avoid the panic-buying trap on secondary markets. Good luck.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
</BaseLayout>
